report_text: right internal jugular central venous catheter tip terminates in the mid svc . moderate to severe cardiomegaly is re- demonstrated . the mediastinal and hilar contours are unchanged . moderate pulmonary edema is slightly worse in the interval . small right pleural effusion is unchanged . bibasilar airspace opacities likely reflect atelectasis . no pneumothorax is identified . there are no acute osseous abnormalities .
